npm-packages/
# Root tests/ holds Playwright specs, Node E2E and node-based unit tests - none
# of it is Meteor code, and Meteor's file watcher otherwise churns on the
# tests/playwright/test-results/ tree (inotify errors). The leading slash anchors
# this to the repo root only, so it does NOT match server/lib/tests/ or
# client/lib/tests/ (the Mocha suites, loaded via meteor.testModule in
# package.json). A naked "tests/" would match a dir named tests at any depth and
# would hide those suites, making `meteor test` report "0 passing".
/tests/

# Build/tool scratch space: a full Node 24 install (headers for EVERY openssl arch),
# a Go toolchain with its module/build caches, build logs and repro dirs. 20,535
# DIRECTORIES, none of it app code. Meteor's watcher takes one inotify watch per
# directory, and the per-user limit (fs.inotify.max_user_watches, 65536 here) is
# shared with every other watcher the user runs - editors included. Watching this
# tree is what made `meteor` fail with
#   inotify_add_watch on '.tools/node-.../openssl/archs/BSD-x86_64/asm_avx2'
#   failed: No space left on device
# ENOSPC from inotify_add_watch means "watch limit reached", NOT a full disk.
/.tools/

# The FerretDB v1 fork checkout: a complete Go project + its docs, 9,148 more
# directories. Nothing in WeKan imports from it - the FerretDB binary is
# downloaded from its GitHub releases at build time - so Meteor has no reason to
# watch or scan it. Both are already in .gitignore, but the watcher only honours
# .meteorignore.
/FerretDB/
